recalls.Summary: Chrysler (FCA US LLC) is recalling certain model year 2013-2014 Dodge Viper vehicles manufactured October 1, 2012, to February 6, 2014.  Moisture may get into the door switch, resulting in the driver or passenger door opening unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion.
recalls.Consequence: If the driver or passenger door opens unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion, there is an increased risk of a crash and injury.
recalls.Remedy: Chrysler will notify owners, and dealers will replace the door handle assemblies and top covers, free of charge. The recall began on July 10, 2015.  Owners may contact Chrysler customer service at 1-800-853-1403. Chrysler's number for this recall is R14.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Chrysler (FCA US LLC) is recalling certain model year 2013-2015 Ram 1500, 2500, 3500, 4500, and 5500, 2015 Chrysler 200, Chrysler 300, Dodge Charger, and Dodge Challenger, 2014-2015 Jeep Grand Cherokee, Cherokee, and Dodge Durango, and 2013-2015 Dodge Viper vehicles.  The affected vehicles are equipped with radios that have software vulnerabilities that can allow third-party access to certain networked vehicle control systems.
recalls.Consequence: Exploitation of the software vulnerability may result in unauthorized remote modification and control of certain vehicle systems, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Chrysler will notify and mail affected owners a USB drive that includes a software update that eliminates the vulnerability, free of charge.  Optionally, owners may download the update to their own USB drive from http://www.driveuconnect.com/software-update/ or take their vehicle to a Chrysler dealer for immediate installation.  In an effort to mitigate the effects of this security vulnerability, Chrysler has had the wireless service provider close the open cellular connection to the vehicle that provided unauthorized access to the vehicle network.   This measure may not have been implemented on all vehicles and does not address access by other means that will be remedied by the software update.  The recall began on August 25, 2015.  Owners may contact Chrysler customer service at 1-800-853-1403.  Chrysler's number for this recall is R40.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

complaints.summary: AS MANY 2013-2015 DODGE VIPER OWNERS REPORT ONLINE, THE HORN TURNS ON AND OFF, STICKING ON FOR LONG PERIODS OF TIME WITH NO CONTACT, RANDOMLY. MOST VIPER OWNER OF THIS YEAR MODEL ARE PULLING THE FUSE SO THE HORN DOES NOT WORK AT ALL. THIS IS A PART OF THE STEERING WHEEL AIRBAG ASSEMBLY THAT IS TIED IN WITH THE HORN MECHANISM. THIS IS A KNOWN PROBLEM WITH THESE VERY EXPENSIVE SIX FIGURE VEHICLES AND SHOULD BE ADDRESSED AS A SAFETY CONCERN BY DODGE IMMEDIATELY AS A RECALL AS THIS IS NEEDED FOR STATE SAFETY INSPECTION.

I WAS DRIVING MY CAR AND SOMETHING LIKE A RUBBER/ELECTRICAL SMELL WAS NOTICED.  I LOOKED IN MY REARVIEW MIRROR AND SEEN I HAD SMOKE FILLING THE REAR OF THE CAR.  I IMMEDIATELY PULLED OVER.  GOT OUT AND OPENED THE REAR LIFT GATE AND AS I LOOKED TO SEE WHAT WAS GOING ON MY REAR LIFT GATE GLASS EXPLODED INTO A MILLION PIECES.  IT WAS AS LOUD AS A SHOTGUN GOING OFF.  I WAS VERY LUCKY I HAD STOPPED MY CAR AS IT COULD POSSIBLY HAVE CAUSE ME OR SOMEONE DRIVING BEHIND ME TO HAVE AN ACCIDENT IF I HAD BEEN TRAVELING DOWN THE ROAD.  THERE WASN'T A PIECE OF GLASS NO BIGGER THAN A DIME LEFT OF THE REAR GLASS.  I WAS VERY FORTUNATE THAT I DIDN'T GET CUT OR GLASS IN MY EYES.  SHORTLY AFTER IT HAPPENED I REMEMBERED THAT IF THE REAR DEFROSTER WAS TURNED ON THAT THE REAR GLASS COULD EXPLODE OUT.  I THEN REMEMBERED THAT I WAS IN THE PROCESS OF CHANGING THE RADIO CHANNEL AND MUST HAVE TOUCHED THE BUTTON FOR THE REAR DEFROSTER.  MY DASH SCREEN WAS DIMMED SINCE I WAS RUNNING MY PARKING LIGHTS AND COULD NOT SEE MY RADIO BUTTONS AND INSTEAD PRESSED THE BUTTON TURNING ON THE REAR DEFROSTER INSTEAD OF TRYING TO CHANGE THE RADIO CHANNEL.  SOMETHING ABOUT IF THE CARBON FIBER PANELING WAS TOUCHING THE GLASS IT COULD CAUSE A MISHAP.  I CONTACTED MY DEALERSHIP AND THEY SAID THERE WASN'T A RECALL ON IT AND THAT THERE WASN'T ANYTHING THEY COULD DO ABOUT IT AND THAT THERE WAS ONLY A TECHNICAL SERVICE BULLETIN ABOUT IT.  THIS IS TOTALLY UNACCEPTABLE AND THEY SHOULD BE REQUIRED TO DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT.  NOW I HAVE TO PAY TO REPLACE MY GLASS AND ALSO I'LL NEVER BE ABLE TO USE MY DEFROSTER IN THE FUTURE.  SOMETHING SHOULD BE DONE ABOUT THIS BEFORE THIS HAPPENS TO SOMEONE ELSE OR WORSE CAUSE SOMEONE TO HAVE A TERRIBLE ACCIDENT.  I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHY THE DEALERSHIP NEVER ENSURED MY CAR WAS UPDATED TO PREVENT THIS FROM EVER HAPPENING.  FCA SHOULD TAKE RESPONSIBILITY AND CORRECT THIS SERIOUS PROBLEM ASAP.  *TR

TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2013 DODGE VIPER. THE CONTACT STATED THAT WHILE DRIVING AT 70 MPH, THE ROOF SEPARATED FROM THE VEHICLE. THE VEHICLE WAS TOWED TO LEE CHRYSLER DODGE JEEP RAM LOCATED AT: 3700 RALEIGH ROAD PARKWAY W, WILSON, NC 27896, TEL: (855)217-8742 TO BE DIAGNOSED. THE CONTACT WAS INFORMED THAT DURING PRODUCTION, ADHESIVE WAS NOT ADDED TO THE SUB FRAME AND THE CARBON FIBER ROOF CAUSING AIR TO GET UP UNDER THE CARBON FIBER CAUSING THE SEPARATION. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE APPROXIMATE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 6,700.

I OWN A 2013 DODGE VIPER SRT, TURNED ON MY REAR HATCH WINDOW DEFROSTER WHILE DRIVING TO CLEAR MY REAR WINDOW FOR THE FIRST TIME AND SMOKE STARTING COMING FROM REAR HATCH AREA. I QUICKLY RUSHED TO TURN IF OFF, THE SMOKE STARTED TO CLEAR. SECONDS AFTER MY REAR HATCH WINDOW SHATTER. A LOUD POP NOISE WAS HEAR AT THE TIME OF SHATTERING, ALMOST LIKE AN EXPLOSION. I QUICKLY TURNED BACK HOME AND PARKED THE VEHICLE. IT IS NOW AT THE DEALER AND DODGE IS NOT OWNING UP TO THE ISSUE.  *TR

issues.title: Engine Overheating Due to Faulty Thermostat
issues.description: The thermostat fails to open properly, causing the engine to overheat. This is particularly common in track use or high-performance driving conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace thermostat and housing, flush cooling system, check for additional cooling system damage
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, avoid prolonged high-RPM operation without proper cooling

issues.title: Transmission Fluid Leak from Bell Housing
issues.description: Manual transmission develops leaks at the bell housing area, particularly affecting the Tremec TR6060 transmission used in these models.
issues.fix_description: Replace transmission input shaft seal, inspect clutch components, refill transmission fluid
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive launches

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Hood Delamination
issues.description: The carbon fiber hood develops delamination issues where the carbon fiber layers separate, particularly around the heat vents and edges.
symptoms: Visible separation of carbon fiber layers
issues.fix_description: Replace carbon fiber hood assembly or professional carbon fiber repair
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, use car cover, regular inspection

issues.title: Side Exhaust Heat Shield Failure
issues.description: Heat shields on side exhaust system fail or become loose, creating potential safety hazards and allowing excessive heat near fuel lines.
issues.fix_description: Replace or repair heat shield assemblies, ensure proper mounting hardware
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of exhaust system, avoid driving through deep water

issues.title: ECU Programming Issues Causing Rough Idle
issues.description: Engine control unit programming causes rough idle, stalling, and poor throttle response, particularly in early production models.
issues.fix_description: ECU software update or reprogramming, possible throttle body cleaning
issues.prevention: Keep ECU software updated, regular maintenance

issues.title: Clutch Pedal Linkage Failure
issues.description: The clutch pedal linkage can fail, resulting in inability to disengage the clutch and potential stranding of the vehicle.
symptoms: Grinding noise when attempting to shift
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch master cylinder, slave cylinder, or linkage components as needed
issues.prevention: Regular clutch system inspection, avoid riding the clutch

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Interior and exterior door handles fail to operate properly due to cable stretch or mechanism wear.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism, cables, and related hardware
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, regular lubrication

issues.title: Fuel Rail Pressure Sensor Failure
issues.description: Fuel rail pressure sensor fails causing poor engine performance, rough running, and potential fuel system issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel rail pressure sensor, clear diagnostic codes, test fuel system pressure
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: A/C compressor fails prematurely, often due to contamination or electrical issues, resulting in no cooling.
issues.fix_description: Replace A/C compressor, flush system, replace receiver/dryer, recharge system
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system service, run A/C periodically during winter

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS) Malfunction
issues.description: TPMS sensors fail or provide inaccurate readings, causing warning lights and potential safety concerns.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty TPMS sensors, reprogram system, check for proper tire pressure
issues.prevention: Regular tire maintenance, careful tire mounting/dismounting

editorial.tagline: Raw American fury with zero compromises
editorial.hero_blurb: The final-generation Viper represents the purest expression of American supercar excess. With 645 horsepower from its naturally aspirated 8.4L V10, this is driving in its most primal form.
editorial.essence: The 2013-2017 Viper is an uncompromising weapon that prioritizes visceral thrills over creature comforts. It's the last of a dying breed - a naturally aspirated monster that demands respect and rewards skill with an intoxicating blend of power and precision.
editorial.heritage: Born from Dodge's desire to create an American Cobra, the Viper debuted in 1992 as a no-nonsense sports car. The final generation refined the formula while maintaining the raw character that made it legendary, ending production in 2017 as emissions regulations sealed its fate.
editorial.design_philosophy: Strip away everything unnecessary and amplify what remains. The designers focused on creating the most direct connection between driver and machine, with aerodynamics serving performance rather than aesthetics.
editorial.motorsport_history: Dominated GT racing with multiple ALMS championships and Le Mans class victories. The Viper ACR set numerous lap records at tracks worldwide, proving that American engineering could match European precision on the world's most demanding circuits.
editorial.engine_character: The 8.4L V10 is a masterpiece of naturally aspirated savagery, delivering linear power with an intoxicating crescendo that peaks at 6,200 RPM. Every throttle input is met with immediate, violent response and a soundtrack that borders on religious experience.
editorial.transmission_feel: The six-speed manual is deliberately heavy and mechanical, requiring deliberate inputs that connect you directly to the drivetrain. Each shift feels like operating industrial machinery - purposeful, substantial, and utterly engaging.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Razor-sharp and unforgiving, the chassis communicates every nuance of the road surface. It rewards smooth inputs with devastating cornering ability but punishes ham-fisted driving with snap oversteer that separates the skilled from the foolish.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulically assisted steering provides unfiltered feedback with just enough assistance to prevent arm fatigue. Every tire patch detail transmits through the wheel, creating an almost telepathic connection to the front wheels.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo brakes deliver fade-free stopping power with a firm, progressive pedal that inspires complete confidence even at triple-digit speeds. The ABS is calibrated to allow threshold braking while preventing lockup.
editorial.sound_signature: A primal roar that starts as a menacing rumble at idle and builds to a spine-tingling wail at redline. The side-exit exhausts create a symphony of mechanical fury that announces your presence from miles away.
editorial.ideal_owner: Experienced enthusiasts who crave unfiltered driving experiences and have the skill to handle a car that doesn't suffer fools. Perfect for collectors who appreciate American engineering excellence and track day warriors who want maximum thrills.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Casual drivers, comfort seekers, or anyone wanting daily driver practicality. The Viper demands respect and skill - it's not forgiving to inexperience or inattention.
editorial.buyers_summary: Buy the best example you can afford and budget for maintenance - these are hand-built supercars, not mass-produced vehicles. The ACR variants are already appreciating rapidly, but even base models represent incredible performance value.

expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 Dodge Viper successfully resurrects the legendary nameplate with modern engineering while preserving its raw American muscle car DNA. With 720 horsepower from a naturally aspirated V10, manual transmission, and improved chassis dynamics, it offers an authentic driving experience in a world of turbocharged alternatives. Starting around $125,000, it positions itself as an attainable supercar that celebrates uncompromising performance over luxury refinement.

expertReviews.title: Driving the Last Dodge Viper || A Review 10 Years Later
pros: 8.4L V10 engine with incredible torque delivery and sound
Engaging manual transmission that requires skill and provides satisfaction
Exceptional track performance with adjustable Bilstein suspension
Unique and aggressive styling that stands out
One of the most affordable cars capable of 206 mph top speed
Well-designed interior with proper physical controls
Massive rear tires provide excellent traction in higher gears
cons: Very heavy and difficult clutch operation
Requires significant physical effort to drive spiritedly
Weight distribution causes front-heavy feel during cornering
Poor rearward visibility
Early generations had dangerous handling characteristics
expertReviews.verdict: The fifth-generation Dodge Viper represents a final masterpiece of traditional sports car engineering - a naturally aspirated V10 with manual transmission that's become irreplaceable in today's automotive landscape. Despite being over a decade old, it not only competes with modern cars but surpasses them in delivering a pure, engaging driving experience. The reviewer concludes this is 'one of the greatest production cars ever made' that makes you a better driver while providing unmatched sensory stimulation.

expertReviews.title: The 2005 Dodge Viper SRT-10 Is a Crazy Exotic Car Bargain
pros: 500 horsepower 8.3L V10 engine with massive displacement
Excellent value - sells for $30-50k range with exotic car performance
Under 4 seconds 0-60 time with less than 3,400 lb weight
Manual transmission only maintains pure driving experience
Great bolstered Alcantara seats with racing harness provisions
Cool exterior design elements like side vents and hidden door handles
cons: Cheap interior materials with plastic everywhere despite $80k original price
Side exhaust pipes make entering/exiting difficult due to heat
Manual convertible top requires getting out of car to operate
Styling too tame compared to previous aggressive Viper generations
Poor quality details like exposed screws and basic switches
Single small unusable cup holder
expertReviews.verdict: The 2005 Viper SRT-10 represents an incredible performance bargain, delivering exotic car acceleration and 500hp V10 thrills at half the price of European competitors. While the interior quality is deliberately cheap to keep costs down, and the styling is less aggressive than previous Vipers, it still offers a unique manual-only, rear-wheel-drive experience that's become increasingly rare. The side exhaust heat issues and manual top operation are annoying but the core driving experience and value proposition make it a compelling choice for performance enthusiasts.

expertReviews.title: 2017 Dodge Viper GTC Review | The Best Thing Dodge Has ...
pros: 8.4L naturally aspirated V10 with 645hp and 600 lb-ft torque
One-of-one GTC customization program with 50 million possible combinations
Exceptional steering feel described as 'telepathic'
Track-capable performance that can compete with exotic cars
Tremec 6-speed manual transmission feels natural and comfortable
Timeless design that has aged very well
Raw, old-school mechanical driving experience
Custom Ferrari Rosso Fuco paint and premium Laguna leather interior
cons: Tight pedal box with offset ergonomics
Hot exhaust routing under the wide doors
Can be unforgiving and will 'bite' inexperienced drivers
Limited red line at 6,400 RPM due to massive displacement
No automatic transmission option available
expertReviews.verdict: The 2017 Dodge Viper GTC represents the pinnacle of old-school American performance, offering a truly unique one-of-one customization experience. With its massive 8.4L V10, telepathic steering, and track-proven capabilities, it delivers an irreplaceable driving experience that modern digitized supercars can't match. While it requires respect and skill to drive properly, it rewards drivers with pure mechanical performance that can compete with European exotics at multiple times the price. The GTC program's extensive customization options and handbuilt nature make each car truly special.
